%global __brp_check_rpaths %{nil}
%global packname  RSE
%global packver   1.3
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.3
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Number of Newly Discovered Rare Species Estimation

License:          GPL-3
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
A Bayesian-weighted estimator and two unweighted estimators are developed
to estimate the number of newly found rare species in additional
ecological samples. Among these methods, the Bayesian-weighted estimator
and an unweighted (Chao-derived) estimator are of high accuracy and
recommended for practical applications. Technical details of the proposed
estimators have been well described in the following paper: Shen TJ, Chen
YH (2018) A Bayesian weighted approach to predicting the number of newly
discovered rare species. Conservation Biology, In press.

%prep
%setup -q -c -n %{packname}


